Kaizer Chiefs have confirmed that they will play Elgeco Plus at the Moses Mabhida Stadium in Durban. Chiefs progressed through to the next round of the CAF Confederation Cup competition, after defeating Zimamoto on 4-3 on aggregate in the preliminary round.The Soweto giants will now lock horns with Elgeco on on Saturday, 15 December.“Kaizer Chiefs will host Madagascar’s Elgeco at Durban’s Moses Mabhida Stadium on Saturday, 15 December 2018. Kick-off is at 20:15,” Chiefs confirmed on their official website.The Soweto giants will be without two of their first team players for several weeks, with Ramahlwe Mphahlele ruled out of action for up to two months, while Erick Mathoho will also be sidelined for three. 